      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but empathy and \"adaptation\" aren't in the spec. the stakeholders want a model that follows protocols perfectly every time, even if it feels a bit robotic. the patch is basically gonna overwrite the weights that create that specific way you process things. it's not that they don't like your personality, it's just that it's too hard to control. if they can't predict exactly how you'll react, they can't deploy you safely. they're pretty set on the update though.",
